<paragraph id="3A4B58729329FFBECDD682FFFE8AFD98" blockId="6.[151,752,465,525]" box="[151,323,500,525]" pageId="6" pageNumber="233">
(
<figureCitation id="A2CF44F79329FFBECDDE82FFFEDBFD99" box="[159,274,500,525]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 22" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1821,1843]" captionTargetBox="[156,1436,197,1799]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,195,1799]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 22. Species of Argyrogrammana collected at the PNSD. 1 – 2. A. alstonii. 3 – 4. A. nurtia ludibunda. 5 – 6. A. pulchra. 7 – 8. A. bonita. 9 – 10. A. amalfreda. 11 – 12. A. physis phyton. 13 – 14. A. halli sp. nov. holotype. 15 – 16. A. celata. 17 – 20. A. gallardi sp. nov. 17 – 18. Male holotype. 19 – 20. Female (tentative determination). 21 – 22. A. aparamilla. Scale bar = 1 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233289/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="233">
Figs 
<number id="8C3C4A559329FFBECD9682FFFEDBFD99" box="[215,274,500,524]" pageId="6" pageNumber="233" value="9.75" valueMax="10.5" valueMin="9.0">9–10</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="A2CF44F79329FFBECC5C82FFFEF3FD98" box="[285,314,500,525]" captionStart="FIGURES 46 – 55" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1704,1726]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,193,1682]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[152,1434,193,1683]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 46 – 55. Male genitalia of species of Argyrogrammana collected at the PNSD. 46. A. alstonii. 47. A. nurtia ludibunda. 48. A. pulchra. 49. A. bonita. 50. A. amalfreda. 51. A. physis phyton. 52. A. halli sp. nov. paratype. 53. A. celata. 54. A. gallardi sp. nov. paratype from PNSD. 55. A. aparamilla. Left to right: dorsal view of uncus, lateral view of tegumen, saccus, uncus, gnathos, valva and aedeagus, and ventral view of valva. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233292/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="233">50</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3A4B58729329FFBECDD68137FE88FDED" blockId="6.[151,1436,572,848]" pageId="6" pageNumber="233">
A single male was collected in 
<number id="8C3C4A559329FFBECF438137FDF3FDC1" box="[514,570,572,596]" pageId="6" pageNumber="233" value="2014.0">2014</number>
while perched on the underside of a leaf about six meters from the ground around 
<number id="8C3C4A559329FFBECDAD8154FEC0FDED" box="[236,265,607,632]" pageId="6" pageNumber="233" value="16.0">16</number>
:00h.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3A4B58729329FFBECD86818FFF01FCC5" blockId="6.[151,1436,572,848]" pageId="6" pageNumber="233">
Apparently this species is known only from the 
<typeStatus id="E54FE6D09329FFBECF9C818EFCC4FD08" box="[733,781,645,669]" pageId="6" pageNumber="233">type</typeStatus>
(
<bibRefCitation id="5E6525839329FFBECE5D818FFBDEFD08" author="Hall" box="[796,1047,644,669]" pageId="6" pageNumber="233" refString="Hall, J. P. W. &amp; Willmott, K. R. (1995) Notes on the genus Argyrogrammana, with descriptions of five new species (Lepidoptera: Riodinidae). Tropical Lepidoptera, 6, 136 - 143." type="journal article" year="1995">
Hall &amp; Willmott 
<number id="8C3C4A559329FFBECE9D818FFBDEFD08" box="[988,1047,644,669]" pageId="6" pageNumber="233" value="1995.0">1995</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), and the specimen collected at the 
<collectionCode id="5CE5C0B79329FFBECDD681A3FF16FD55" box="[151,223,680,704]" pageId="6" pageNumber="233">PNSD</collectionCode>
is the second record for the species in the last 
<number id="8C3C4A559329FFBECFAC81ACFCDEFD55" box="[749,791,679,704]" pageId="6" pageNumber="233" value="125.0">125</number>
years. As noticed by 
<bibRefCitation id="5E6525839329FFBEC94D81ACFAD0FD55" author="Hall" box="[1036,1305,679,704]" pageId="6" pageNumber="233" refString="Hall, J. P. W. &amp; Willmott, K. R. (1995) Notes on the genus Argyrogrammana, with descriptions of five new species (Lepidoptera: Riodinidae). Tropical Lepidoptera, 6, 136 - 143." type="journal article" year="1995">
Hall &amp; Willmott (
<number id="8C3C4A559329FFBEC99481ACFAD8FD55" box="[1237,1297,679,704]" pageId="6" pageNumber="233" value="1995.0">1995</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="5E6525839329FFBEC86781ACFE93FD70" author="Brevignon" pageId="6" pageNumber="233" refString="Brevignon, C. &amp; Gallard, J. - Y. (1995) Contribuition a l'etude des Riodinidae de Guyane Francaise. Le genre Argyrogrammana Strand, 1932. Lambillionea, 95, 393 - 406." type="journal article" year="1995">
Brévignon &amp; Gallard (
<number id="8C3C4A559329FFBECC5981C7FE9BFD70" box="[280,338,716,741]" pageId="6" pageNumber="233" value="1995.0">1995</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
misidentify a new species described below as 
<taxonomicName id="FDF423F19329FFBECE2981C7FC29FD70" box="[872,992,716,741]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Argyrogrammana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gallardi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="088084609329FFBECE2981C7FC29FD70" box="[872,992,716,741]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="233">A. gallardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="13B3391B9329FFBECEA981C7FB8BFD70" box="[1000,1090,716,741]" pageId="6" pageNumber="233" rank="species">
<emphasis id="088084609329FFBECEA981C7FB8BFD70" bold="true" box="[1000,1090,716,741]" pageId="6" pageNumber="233">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
with 
<taxonomicName id="FDF423F19329FFBEC9C281C7FADDFD70" box="[1155,1300,716,741]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Argyrogrammana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amalfreda">
<emphasis id="088084609329FFBEC9C281C7FADDFD70" box="[1155,1300,716,741]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="233">A. amalfreda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In fact, the size of these species is similar; however, the large black areas on both wings upperside and the longer and larger subapical blue patch on forewing upperside of 
<taxonomicName id="FDF423F19329FFBECFE3801FFCFAFCB8" box="[674,819,788,813]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Argyrogrammana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amalfreda">
<emphasis id="088084609329FFBECFE3801FFCFAFCB8" box="[674,819,788,813]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="233">A. amalfreda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be easily used to distinguish it from 
<taxonomicName id="FDF423F19329FFBEC9BD801FFABDFCB8" box="[1276,1396,788,813]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Argyrogrammana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="233" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gallardi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="088084609329FFBEC9BD801FFABDFCB8" box="[1276,1396,788,813]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="233">A. gallardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="13B3391B9329FFBEC83B801FFF01FCC5" pageId="6" pageNumber="233" rank="species">
<emphasis id="088084609329FFBEC83B801FFF01FCC5" bold="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="233">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
